<subSubSection id="578387DC7C59DDF47A488B1761B3DD20" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EAFC8FF7900D820ABB97F7B694AE11CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Distribution and phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3AE740D92F5D4FE5A051FDE21FE726C" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="F115F4904194FDB6652610BAE3439296" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">China: Sichuan</emphasis>
(Daocheng, Dechang, Luding, Meigu, Mianning, Muli, Panzhihua, Shimian, Tianquan, Yanbian, Xide); 
<emphasis id="12A49F26605ED3DFE3451F24F8687DC4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Yunnan</emphasis>
(Dali, Eyuan, Heqing, Lijiang, Yangbi, Yongsheng, Zhongdian) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A719F99945350FD0C595266EDED0FBF9" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Distribution map of Begonia taliensis (syn. B. muliensis) Triangles show distribution sites, based on specimens and field surveys and red triangles indicate type locality of B. muliensis (Muli of Sichuan) and B. taliensis (Dali of Yunnan), respectively." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432253" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">9</figureCitation>
). Alt. 1000-3200 m. Flowering July to October, fruiting August to November.
</paragraph>
<caption id="14A77B8E910A9F479FC73A09AE21DE1D" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.153.50805.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/432253" pageId="0" pageNumber="13" start="Figure 9" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="B0CBB5652205902533E43104E461364A" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis id="8FE7798BA39D7E49694AA4770E4FC92B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="13">Figure 9.</emphasis>
